	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1" facs="R 6456-39 (140)"/>
			<p>It seems that <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-337" type="subject">anti-semitic measures</term> are
				becoming more stringent in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1112" type="subject">administration</term>
				and that <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-342" type="subject">anti-semitic propaganda</term> increases
				upon the eastern front. This activity is reported to be encouraged by those <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_romanians"
					>Romanians</term> who have benefited from the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-588" type="subject"
					>confiscations of Jewish property</term> and their forced <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-667"
					type="subject">retirement</term> from <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_romanians">Romanian</term> public life. [...]</p>
			<pb n="2" facs="R 6456-39 (141)"/>
			<p>The question of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jews</term> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798549/romania.html">Romania</placeName> and the war against <ref
					target="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soviet_Union">Soviet Russia</ref> are linked together, as in all <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1027" type="subject">Axis States</term>. This attitude is claimed by
				competent observers to be greatly encouraged by the <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_romanians">Romanian</term> aristocrats, business
				and professional men, who are behind the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-948" type="subject"
					>Government</term> in this attempt. The explanation offered for the support of these classes to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-342" type="subject">anti-semitic propaganda</term> is the fact that they
				are the chief beneficiaries of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-585" type="subject"
					>expropriations</term> of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jewish</term> owned
				properties in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798549/romania.html">Romania</placeName> and that the control of the economic
				and financial life of the country, in which the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject"
					>Jews</term> were claimed to have a great interest, has been taken over by other <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_romanians"
					>Romanians</term>.</p>
